OL,3,CHuge rally to mark 40th anniversary of
OL,4,Cban on unions at GCHQ
OL,6,FIn 1984, Margaret Thatcher's
OL,7,FConservative government banned trade
OL,8,Funions at GCHQ, citing security
OL,9,Fconcerns.
OL,11,FMost workers quit their unions, but 14
OL,12,Frefused as a matter of principle and
OL,13,Fwere sacked.
OL,15,FIn 1997, the newly-elected Labour
OL,16,Fgovernment lifted the ban and they
OL,17,Fwere able to return to work.
OL,19,FTUC general secretary Paul Nowak said
OL,20,Fthe GCHQ dispute has a special place
OL,21,Fin labour movement history.
