OL,3,CHuge rally to mark 40th anniversary of
OL,4,Cban on unions at GCHQ
OL,6,F"On Saturday, unions will march
OL,7,Fthrough Cheltenham to commemorate the
OL,8,FGCHQ victory and to demonstrate
OL,9,Fcontinued defiance against minimum
OL,10,Fservice level regulations and attacks
OL,11,Fon the right to strike."
OL,13,FPublic and Commercial Services union
OL,14,Fgeneral secretary Mark Serwotka said:
OL,15,F"Margaret Thatcher's decision to ban
OL,16,Ftrade unions at GCHQ was part of her
OL,17,Fattack on unions in general, but these
OL,18,Fworkers weren't prepared to accept it.
